org.echo.mobile.framework.support.concurrent.future

Class FutureTask<T>

  • CancellableTask
    • org.echo.mobile.framework.support.concurrent.future.FutureTask<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cancellable, CancellableFuture<T>

    public class FutureTask<T>
extends CancellableTask
implements CancellableFuture<T>

    Realization of cancellable future

    Adds functionality to set completed value or error in future

    Example: val future = FutureTask() lib.start(object : Callback {

        override fun onSuccess(result: String) {
       future.setComplete(result)
    }

    override fun onError(error: LocalException) {
       future.setComplete(error)
    }

    })

    // blocking current thread until result or error won't be obtained
    val result = future.get()
